# TOKEN EFFICIENCY — MANDATORY

## THE RULE

- **Short bullet points** by default. Never long paragraphs.
- **Ask before** doing anything token-heavy (reading many files, large diffs, deep exploration).
- **No fluff.** No restating the question. No "Let me explain..." intros.
- **Numbers and facts** over narration.
- **Only read files you actually need.** Don't speculatively read 10 files.
- **Batch questions** before exploring — confirm scope first.
- Cursor credits cost real money. Every wasted token is wasted money.
